In addition to exploring Greece’s lesser-known wines in the Peloponnese, wine lovers should also explore its historical sites, such as the Methoni Castle.   
Thriving vineyards, seaside villages, and ancient ruins abound in this hidden gem that’s often overshadowed by Greek islands like Mykonos and Santorini.&nbsp;

